
[1]tragical

   TRAG'ICAL, a. [L. tragicus.]

   1. Pertaining to tragedy; of the nature or character of tragedy; as a
   tragic poem; tragic play or representation.

   2. Fatal to life; mournful; sorrowful; calamitous; as the tragic scenes
   of Hayti the tragic horrors of Scio and Missilonghi; the tragical fate
   of the Greeks.

   3. Mournful; expressive of tragedy,the loss of life, or of sorrow.

   I now must change those notes to tragic.
